Hi Ama,

Some of us are heat freaks, so I’m curious what the brand is of the hot salsa that is available where you live (and wonder if I can even get it here in New England). Around here, when it says hot on the jar, it’s barely tepid to anyone that likes hot stuff.

@Mary Beth
I agree with increasing the filling although did very much enjoy per the recipe.  Salt fine and I’m not counting calories so left sugars as suggested.  The dough was quite sticky and dense so spreading bottom layer was not possible with a spatula; moistened fingers seemed to do the trick.  

I placed bottom dough and filling in the freezer for 45 mins and still was not stiff enough for spreading the top dough layer.  I rolled out the top layer between sheets of wax paper and that worked well.  I will make these again.
